sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K195411
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part is composed of pTetR(BBa_R0040),RBS(BBa_B0034),PelB(BBa_J32015),F10scFv(BBa_K195400),C-IgAP(BBa_K195406) and terminator (BBa_B0015)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
The leader sequence of C-IgAP is cleaved at the membrane by a signal peptidase, releasing the mature polyprotein into the periplasm. When in the periplasm, the beta-domain of the protein inserts into the outer membrane to form a beta-barrel structure. After formation of the beta-barrel pore, the passenger domain is translocated to the cell surface through the pore.
Fusion of a scFv to the IgA protease allowed us to investigate the passage of the chimeric protein through the periplasm, its insertion into the outer membrane and the movement of the N-terminal moiety towards the cell surface.
So we can anchor the F10scFv(antibody) on ''E.coli'' 's surface,and catch the influenza A virus.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The PelB+scFv+C-IgAP didn't have any scar,so we used PCR to In-fusion.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Syue-Liang Lin

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: F10scFv
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Our antibody (F10scFv) can bind to the highly conserved region in HA on many subtypes of the Influenza A virus. F10scFv binds to a common epitope that is a highly conserved pocket in the stem region of Hemagglutinin containing the fusion peptide.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Syue-Liang Lin

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: C-IgAP
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: When in the periplasm, the beta-domain(C-terminal) of the protein inserts into the outer membrane to form a beta-barrel structure. After formation of the beta-barrel pore, the passenger domain is translocated to the cell surface through the pore. Once at the cell surface, several possibilities may occur.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: C-IgAP(BBa_J32018) is exist part,but this part is not exist in plate. We need to PCR this sequence from Neisseria gonorrhoeae by ourself. There have some problem:Pst1 cutting site...So we have to mutate these site dierectly.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Syue-Liang Lin

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: PelB
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: PelB leader sequence; directs protein to E. coli periplasmic membrane
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The pelB leader sequence is a sequence of amino acids which when attached to a protein, directs the protein to the periplasmic membrane of E. coli, where the sequence is removed by pelB peptidase. It is used to direct coat protein-antigen fusions to the cell surface.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Austen Heinz
